Clop Ransomware came forward with a record-breaking H1 2025 campaign, which utilized significant zero-day weaknesses in CLEO Managed File Transfer (MFT) solutions (CVE-2024-50623 and CVE-2024-555956). The group was responsible for 35% of all victims listed on data types alone in February, which marks an increase of 1400% in activity compared to the end of 2024. 

Clop targeted mainly organizations in production, retail and transport sectors with heavy concentration in the United States (72%). Known for the operation of its burst style, Clops' strategy includes data ex filing, resolution of the supply chain and demand for Silavya, making it one of the most impressive Rangesware groups at the beginning of 2025.
